premise_source_doc_sentence: In 70 , he besieged and captured Jerusalem , and destroyed the city and the Second Temple .
The Second Temple period in Jewish history lasted between 530 BCE and 70 CE , when the Second Temple of Jerusalem existed .
The Second Temple period ended with the First Jewish -- Roman War and the Roman destruction of Jerusalem and the Temple .

Jerusalem during the Second Temple period describes the history of the city from the return to Zion under Cyrus the Great to the 70 CE siege of Jerusalem by Titus during the First Jewish -- Roman War , which saw both region and city change hands several times .
